==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polishing
<hw>Pol"ish*ing</hw>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos> from
<er>Polish</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Polishing iron</b></col>, <cd>an iron burnisher; esp., a
small smoothing iron used in laundries.</cd> -- <col><b>Polishing
slate</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>A gray or yellow slate, found in
Bohemia and Auvergne, and used for polishing glass, marble, and
metals</cd>. <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>A kind of hone or whetstone; hone
slate.</cd> -- <col><b>Polishing snake</b></col>, <cd>a tool used in
cleaning lithographic stones.</cd> -- <col><b>Polishing wheel</b></col>,
<cd>a wheel or disk coated with, or composed of, abrading material, for
polishing a surface.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polishment</ent>⟦br⟧
